            Red, white, purple, black? Choosing a Remembrance Day poppy
            The red poppy signifies a memorial to those who died in World War One.It was adopted by the Royal British Legion in 1921.While many wear the traditional red poppy ahead of Remembrance Day, some opt for a white, black or even a purple flower.But what do the different coloured poppies mean?
                
                        28 Oct 2016
                    
                
        
